es the complex process and language of incrimination, reflecting on its literary, philosophical, social, and political manifestations in the texts and contexts of the five novels. She looks for signs of possible subversion of the incriminating process within the texts: Can female protagonists (and women writers) escape the vicious circling of the story that would incriminate them? In the course of this book, the stories are made to reveal their strikingly modern and postmodern preoccupations with survival.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFeminism and literature. 0aFictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aFictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGuilt in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400821310zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400821310423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781400821310/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK